Note: The validation and session management is most always going to be the exact same steps


Logging In:
Has three possible outcomes:
1. The email the user inputted isnt in our database. RESULT: Send the user back to the form
2. there is an account with the email given but the password is not matching the one saved in the database. RESULT: Send the user back to the form
3. the email the user inputted is correct and the password the user inputted matches the one in the database.

Session is persistent data that I can use in all my routes as long as my session is validation